<p>Chapter 1
Introduction</p>
<p>1.1    Introduction
The proposed service management system is an intelligent application that provides many features such as it offers verified professional home service workers connecting directly with households. It contains different categories targeting all levels of users including electricians, plumbers, home appliance repairers, and regular laborers. Those features are all integrated to attract customers with their various daily problems. We aim to be a point of confidence among the community with high service quality, verified backgrounds (KYC), and instant communication with users in general. Furthermore, it utilizes Socket.io to be more flexible and elastic in communication queries and has a robust security system to make users feel confident to share their locations. Applications in general can facilitate people's lives faster. We worked with everything we could to simplify our application in the form of a gig-economy marketplace so that people in our dear country can keep pace with technological development.</p>
<p>Smart Home Services Management System is divided into three modules-
    Admin
    User (Resident)
    Provider</p>
<p>Admins Features:
    Admins Dashboard via Web browser.
    Admins can add/edit and delete service categories.
    Admins can calculate and track platform commissions.
    Admins can verify Service Provider KYC (Know Your Customer) documentation.
    Admins can search all users by a search field.
    Admins can view all system bookings and resolve disputes.</p>
<p>User &amp; Provider Features:
     User can register themselves via an OTP system and after registration they will login by email/password.
    After login, Resident or Provider can view their respective dashboards.
    User can fetch exact Geolocation via GPS to send providers accurate addresses.
    User can read job description and provider's reviews from their dashboard.
    Provider can Accept, Reject, or Complete active jobs.
    Real-time chat enables Resident and Provider to talk instantly inside the app.</p>
<p>1.2 Objectives of the Project
The main objectives of this projects are:
    To develop customer trust in local home service laborers.
    To deploy a highly scalable app using the MERN stack and React Native.
    To develop an instant searching and chat feature. 
    To provide a transparent, GPS-driven, secure environment.
    Prevent time-wasting in physically looking for handymen.</p>
<p>1.3 Organization of the Project
In this project we have developed an Android based online Service Management Application along with a React.js Admin backend. It is a dynamic system that can easily be maintained and modified due to its NoSQL database nature. The application generates results in real time, incorporating Javascript source code. It is designed to ensure complete security against unauthorized access, providing a safe environment. 
This application leverages JSON as one of the main payload structures for data exchange, enabling the creation of interactive and customizable user interfaces. React components play a crucial role in structuring and organizing the screens within the application, ensuring efficient data management. 
To develop the application, we have adopted the incremental model, which allows adding features like Sockets and Maps at different stages of development. </p>
<p>1.4 Programming Languages
    JavaScript and Node.js using for backend server logic.
    React JSX using for frontend web UI.
    React Native using for mobile Android Application.
    MongoDB for storing data entities.
    Socket.io for Realtime data messaging.</p>
<p>1.5 Background of Project
Smart Home Services is a digital marketplace that stocks a range of everyday service professionals such as plumbers, electricians, and cleaners. This app differs from traditional classifieds in that they are actively tracked in real-time. From the app, users can easily purchase local service visits. Admins can moderate the platform safely via the web client.</p>
<p>1.6 Operational Environment
ANDROID     OS 8.0 or completely updated iOS.
RAM            3 GB OR MORE SMART DEVICE
SERVER      Node.js Server Runtime Environment
DATABASE    MongoDB Cloud Atlas</p>
<p>1.7 Advantages
    Booking local home services online is cost-effective as it allows price negotiations beforehand.
    The app is very convenient. Not only does it make physical travel unnecessary, but it simplifies the process of tracking your worker on a map.
    With Provider KYC verified, safety and peace of mind are significantly enhanced over calling random unverified workers into a house.
    The system allows a real-time Chat interface avoiding expensive GSM phone calls.</p>
<p>1.8 Disadvantages
    As with most online gig-economy transactions, a level of trust is still required before letting a stranger into a private home.
    For workers (Providers), keeping GPS running actively consumes battery life.
    Requires active and stable internet connection throughout the transaction (to send start/complete status signals).</p>
<p>Chapter 2
System Analysis</p>
<p>2.1 Software Requirement Specification</p>
<p>2.1.1 General Description</p>
<p>This chapter will cover the software requirements specification (SRS), a comparison of the existing and proposed systems, and an analysis of the Smart Home Services development process. Before beginning development, the SRS section contains both functional and non-functional requirements to give a thorough explanation and overview of the system requirements. </p>
<p>Problem Statement :</p>
<p>Taking into account the parameters, the home service industry is massive but extremely unorganized. We all require plumbers or electricians for sudden domestic emergencies. Searching for professional help has traditionally been slow and unreliable. For a variety of reasons, including high-pressure jobs, managing home maintenance is exhausting. However, there are certain difficulties with online home service delivery that both customers and service providers encounter over time, such as trust issues, fair pricing, and exact location tracking. Long work hours are pushing homeowners toward the convenience of apps to dispatch handymen. </p>
<p>2.1.2 System Objectives</p>
<pre><code>The main goal is to improve the speed of resolving home maintenance issues.
It saves the effort required to physically find available workers.
It introduces a fair commission and wallet system to digitize gig-working.
User will be able to select the interested service category and chat with the provider instantly.
</code></pre>
<p>2.1.3 System Requirements</p>
<p>2.1.3.1 Functional Requirements:</p>
<p>Table 1 Functional Requirements
No    Requirements    Description
FR1    User Registration   When making an account, the user enters details including Email, Phone, and Password, strictly verified by OTP.
FR2    User Login  User clicks on login button, puts email and password, returning a secure JWT token.
FR3    Admin Actions       Admin can add new service categories and approve Provider documents.
FR4    Search/Post Jobs    Resident can post a job specifying address, time, and service type. 
FR5    Provider Accept     Provider can view nearby jobs and select Accept or Reject.
FR6    Live Chat           Once accepted, a socket connection opens for real-time text chatting.
FR7    Status Updates      Admins and Providers can change order status (Pending → Completed).</p>
<p>2.1.3.2 Non-Functional Requirements
 Non-Functional requirement is used to define the performance of system.</p>
<p>Table 2 Non Functional Requirements
No    Requirements    Description
NFR1    Performance Response Time: Within two seconds, the application will respond. User interface must be interactive (60 FPS).
NFR2    Reliability The System must be trustworthy using encrypted JWT sessions.
NFR3    Usability   The software mobile app must be easy to navigate using drawer and stack systems.
NFR4    Security    All passwords are systematically hashed (bcrypt).
NFR5    Portability The backend must run anywhere Node.js is installed. </p>
<p>2.1.4 Software and Hardware Requirements</p>
<p>2.1.4.1 Software Requirements</p>
<pre><code>Operating System: The application should be compatible with Android and iOS.
Integrated Development Environment (IDE): VS Code for all React and Express coding.
Programming Languages: JavaScript, JSX.
Backend Development: Node.js and Express framework configuration.
Database Management System: MongoDB NoSQL structure.
Web Services/APIs: Google Maps API or Expo Location API.
</code></pre>
<p>2.1.4.2 Hardware Requirements</p>
<pre><code>Development Machine: A laptop with at least 8GB RAM to run React Native emulators.
Mobile Device: A physical Android device with GPS hardware enabled for thorough testing.
</code></pre>
<p>2.2 Existing System</p>
<p>Right now, when we want to fix a broken pipe or electrical board, we have to ask neighbors or visit a local market to find a technician. Plumbers or electricians usually don't have a structured schedule and might overcharge based on circumstances. Finding verified profiles is extremely difficult. </p>
<p>2.3 Proposed System</p>
<p>To solve the problem with the current system, we have come up with a new way to hire services using our phones. We can easily open the app, drop a pin on our GPS location, and dispatch a request for an electrician. A verified electrician accepts it and uses the map to arrive. Real-time chat helps clarify issues before arrival. When done, payments and commissions are documented transparently. </p>
<p>2.4 Tools and Techniques Used</p>
<p>The whole Project is divided into parts ranging from front-end to backend.</p>
<pre><code>Operating System: Windows, Android OS
IDEs: Visual Studio Code, Android Studio Emulators
Libraries: React.js, React Native, Tailwind/CSS
Backend Tools: Node.js, Express.js, Socket.io
Database: MongoDB, Mongoose
</code></pre>
