<p>Chapter 5
Backend Database and Server Cloud</p>
<p> 
5.1 Node.js &amp; Express</p>
<p>The Smart Home Services Management system relies completely on a Node.js runtime environment. Express.js acts as the fundamental web framework that routes API requests between the Mobile App, Web App, and the Database gracefully.</p>
<p>[ Insert Figure 5.1: Node.js Logo/Architecture Diagram ]</p>
<p>5.2 JWT Authentication</p>
<p>JSON Web Tokens (JWT) allows users to sign up and log in securely. The Express backend generates a cryptographic token upon correct password matching, and this token acts as the user's permanent passport to make authorized changes.</p>
<p>[ Insert Figure 5.2: JWT Auth Flow ]</p>
<p>5.3 MongoDB Realtime Database</p>
<p>MongoDB is a cloud-hosted NoSQL database that lets us store arrays of JSON data efficiently. It is perfect for handling our complex user schemas, varying booking coordinates, and extensive chat arrays.</p>
<p>[ Insert Figure 5.3: MongoDB Atlas Logo ]</p>
<p>5.4 Socket.io Messaging</p>
<p>Socket.io enables real-time, bi-directional communication between web clients and servers. This allows our chat application to instantly deliver messages and booking updates without the user needing to manually refresh.</p>
<p>[ Insert Figure 5.4: Socket.io Flow Diagram ]</p>
