<p>6.2 Test Cases Specifications</p>
<p>6.2.1 Black Box Test
Tests are solely based on functionality and requirements, verifying that when a provider clicks 'Accept', the resident sees 'Accepted' on their end without examining the internal DB queries.</p>
<p>6.2.2 White Box Testing
Checking out the code's internal logic. This involved verifying the Mongoose Schema relationships and ensuring the Commission logic precisely calculates math formulas.</p>
<p>Chapter 7
Conclusion</p>
<p>7.1 Conclusion
The Smart Home Services Management System has been successfully developed to provide a convenient and efficient way for users to manage home maintenance using their mobile devices. The application bridges the gap between verified local technicians and households rapidly. The platform utilizes robust technologies including MERN and React Native to assure speed and scalability.
The application has been tested thoroughly to ensure that it operates effectively, specifically measuring the reliability of the real-time Sockets and MongoDB clusters. The system possesses significant potential to formalize gig-economy work.</p>
<p>7.2 Future Work</p>
<pre><code>Examining the role of AI in quoting price estimates based on images uploaded by the user.
Integrating native Digital Wallets (like Stripe or Google Pay) for direct in-app transactions.
Investigating continuous Background GPS tracking so the resident can see the technician's car moving toward their house in real-time.
Exploring Blockchain strategies to provide totally immutable logs for user review authenticity.
</code></pre>
